Title: $N=2$ and $4$ Super Yang-Mills Theories on $M_4 \times Z_2 \times Z_2$

GeometryAuthors: Bin Chen, Takesi Saito, Hong-Bo Teng, Kunihiko Uehara, Ke Wu

Comments: 13 pages, LaTeX file

Journal-ref: Prog.Theor.Phys. 95 (1996) 1173-1182

We derive the $N=2$ and $4$ super Yang-Mills theories from the viewpoint ofthe $M_4\times Z_2\times Z_2$ gauge theory. Scalars and pseudoscalars appearingin the theories are regarded as gauge fields along the directions on $Z_2\timesZ_2$ discrete space.